commit.message:
Drop support for python 3.3

(Pytest no longer supports python 3.3.)
Setuptools and zc.buildout can now install from wheels!

tox: don't force installation in dev mode

Hopefully this is what was causing spurious errors from detox.

(If you want to install humpty into tox's virtualenv in dev mode, use
``tox --develop``.)

Test coverage.

Test that warning is issued for incompatible wheel

Test with wheel==0.18

Wheel==0.18 writes a pymeta.json instead of pydist.json.
This results in distlib.wheel.Wheel.metadata reading metadata
from the RFC822 formatted data rather than the JSON data.

Relax the strict check for wheel compatibility

When running under py35 or py36, distlib sometimes falsely reports
that some wheels are not binary compatible with the current platform.
See https://bitbucket.org/pypa/distlib/issues/93

Update tox.ini

Drop support for python 2.6
Test under python 3.5 and 3.6
Also test with older version of distlib.

Fixes for newer versions distlib (#1)

Fix EggInfo_Legacy.requires to work with recent versions of distlib.

Always create eggs with zip_safe=False (#3)

There currently seems to be no robust way to determine whether a package
is zip_safe from its wheel.
(Thank you to immerrr for the kick to fix this.)

Fix failing test test_copies_script

Apparently, ``distlib.markers.interpret==0.2.6`` now just prepends the
new hashbang line to the copied script, but does not remove the original
hashbang.

Fix failing test TestEggInfo_Legacy.test_requires

Apparently the latest version of distlib.markers.interpret no
longer handles leading whitespace in the marker string well.

Use pytest-catchlog instead of pytest-capturelog

Capturelog has not been updated in years and triggers warnings from
pytest.

Add travis badge to README

[ci skip]
Fixes for .whls built with older versions of wheel
